      "created": "2022-03-11T08:00:43.846Z",
      "reported_by": null,
      "title": "Prototype Pollution in yargs-parser",
      "npm_advisory_id": null,
      "overview": "Affected versions of `yargs-parser` are vulnerable to prototype pollution. Arguments are not properly sanitized, allowing an attacker to modify the prototype of `Object`, causing the addition or modification of an existing property that will exist on all objects.  \nParsing the argument `--foo.__proto__.bar baz'` adds a `bar` property with value `baz` to all objects. This is only exploitable if attackers have control over the arguments being passed to `yargs-parser`.\n\n\n\n## Recommendation\n\nUpgrade to versions 13.1.2, 15.0.1, 18.1.1 or later.",
      "url": "https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-p9pc-299p-vxgp"
    },
